1
00:01:14,080 --> 00:01:19,009
<i>[Meet Yourself]</i>

2
00:01:19,010 --> 00:01:24,010
<i>[Episode 5]</i>

3
00:01:29,640 --> 00:01:32,239
Granny, where are you going?

4
00:01:32,239 --> 00:01:34,099
I'm going to wash my hair in the kitchen.

5
00:01:34,099 --> 00:01:36,640
Why are you washing your hair in the kitchen?

6
00:01:36,640 --> 00:01:39,760
I forgot to add water to the solar water heater yesterday.

7
00:01:39,760 --> 00:01:42,920
I'm worried you won't have enough water for your bath.

8
00:01:42,920 --> 00:01:44,230
You can go ahead.

9
00:01:44,230 --> 00:01:46,019
I'm fine with cold shower.

10
00:01:46,019 --> 00:01:48,350
That won't do. You might catch a cold.

11
00:01:48,350 --> 00:01:49,950
I'm just washing my hair anyway.

12
00:01:49,950 --> 00:01:52,590
Okay, fine. I'll help you wash your hair.

13
00:01:54,590 --> 00:01:55,939
Did you drink?

14
00:01:55,939 --> 00:01:57,039
Yes.

15
00:01:57,040 --> 00:01:59,400
I drank with Uncle Heshun.

16
00:01:59,870 --> 00:02:01,400
Let's go.

17
00:02:02,750 --> 00:02:04,300
Be careful.

18
00:02:11,150 --> 00:02:12,060
<i>Lower your head.</i>

19
00:02:12,060 --> 00:02:12,749
<i>Okay.</i>

20
00:02:12,749 --> 00:02:14,370
<i>- Be careful.
- Okay.</i>

21
00:02:15,120 --> 00:02:16,750
<i>Be careful.</i>

22
00:02:18,240 --> 00:02:19,399
<i>It's fine.</i>

23
00:02:19,400 --> 00:02:20,810
<i>I'm okay. Pour the water here.</i>

24
00:02:20,810 --> 00:02:22,480
<i>Okay.</i>

25
00:02:22,480 --> 00:02:23,940
<i>Yeah, okay.</i>

26
00:02:24,520 --> 00:02:26,910
<i>- Is the temperature okay?
- Yes.</i>

27
00:02:31,750 --> 00:02:32,699
<i>The temperature is fine, right?</i>

28
00:02:32,699 --> 00:02:34,630
<i>Yeah, it's perfect.</i>

29
00:02:34,630 --> 00:02:36,429
<i>It's nice.</i>

30
00:02:36,430 --> 00:02:39,310
<i>- Okay.
- Okay.</i>

31
00:02:40,010 --> 00:02:42,540
<i>- It's wet now.
- Okay.</i>

32
00:02:42,540 --> 00:02:44,080
<i>Be careful.</i>

33
00:02:45,400 --> 00:02:47,329
<i>- Not bad.
- Okay.</i>

34
00:02:47,329 --> 00:02:49,120
<i>- Pour it on this side.
- Okay.</i>

35
00:02:54,310 --> 00:02:55,430
<i>Granny.</i>

36
00:02:55,430 --> 00:02:57,430
<i>The water isn't hot at all.</i>

37
00:02:57,430 --> 00:03:00,630
<i>There wasn't much sunshine today, so the water isn't hot.</i>

38
00:03:00,630 --> 00:03:02,209
<i>Dry your hair then go to sleep.</i>

39
00:03:02,209 --> 00:03:03,920
<i>Got it.</i>

40
00:03:08,520 --> 00:03:10,530
<i>Your hair isn't dry yet, and you wet the pillow!</i>

41
00:03:10,530 --> 00:03:12,230
<i>How can I sleep now?</i>

42
00:03:12,230 --> 00:03:14,100
<i>Sister, I'll show you something.</i>

43
00:03:14,100 --> 00:03:15,380
<i>What is it?</i>

44
00:03:15,380 --> 00:03:16,750
<i>Where did you get this bug?</i>

45
00:03:16,750 --> 00:03:17,960
<i>This is a single-horned rhinoceros beetle!</i>

46
00:03:17,960 --> 00:03:20,190
<i>Sun Wukong's story has a Single-Horned King!</i>

47
00:03:20,190 --> 00:03:21,430
<i>It's a transformation of this!</i>

48
00:03:21,430 --> 00:03:22,630
<i>That's Journey to the West.</i>

49
00:03:22,630 --> 00:03:24,360
<i>Besides, there wasn't a single-horned king.</i>

50
00:03:24,360 --> 00:03:26,310
<i>There were only the Golden Horn King and Silver Horn King!</i>

51
00:03:26,310 --> 00:03:27,910
<i>Don't be a smart aleck and throw that away!</i>

52
00:03:27,910 --> 00:03:29,680
<i>No, I want to keep it as a pet.</i>

53
00:03:29,680 --> 00:03:31,610
<i>Throw it away!</i>

54
00:03:32,100 --> 00:03:34,000
<i>Give it to me!</i>

55
00:03:34,000 --> 00:03:36,320
<i>Granny, help!</i>

56
00:03:36,320 --> 00:03:39,340
<i>- Give it to me!
- Give it to me!</i>

57
00:03:39,340 --> 00:03:41,750
<i>What is it this time?</i>

58
00:03:41,750 --> 00:03:43,610
<i>Granny! Look at her!</i>

59
00:03:43,630 --> 00:03:45,280
<i>She's keeping a bug on the bed!</i>

60
00:03:45,280 --> 00:03:46,520
<i>It's not a bug!</i>

61
00:03:46,520 --> 00:03:48,560
<i>It's a single-horned rhinoceros beetle I captured!</i>

62
00:03:48,560 --> 00:03:51,240
<i>If you want to keep the bug, then don't sleep with me!</i>

63
00:03:51,240 --> 00:03:52,850
<i>- Give it to me!
- No!</i>

64
00:03:52,850 --> 00:03:54,080
<i>Give it to me!</i>

65
00:03:54,080 --> 00:03:57,000
<i>- Granny!
- Enough, stop fighting!</i>

66
00:03:57,000 --> 00:03:58,060
<i>Granny!</i>

67
00:03:58,060 --> 00:03:59,030
<i>Give it to me!</i>

68
00:03:59,030 --> 00:04:00,120
<i>Granny!</i>

69
00:04:00,120 --> 00:04:01,190
<i>Fine, fight all you want.</i>

70
00:04:01,190 --> 00:04:02,149
<i>Keep fighting.</i>

71
00:04:02,150 --> 00:04:03,960
<i>I'll leave you two be. Fight all you want.</i>

72
00:04:03,960 --> 00:04:05,800
<i>Just keep fighting.</i>

73
00:04:05,800 --> 00:04:08,100
<i>Granny!</i>

74
00:04:21,410 --> 00:04:23,559
<i>Why did you open your eyes again?</i>

75
00:04:23,560 --> 00:04:25,110
<i>Sleep.</i>

76
00:04:25,110 --> 00:04:27,770
<i>Granny, I don't want to go home.</i>

77
00:04:27,770 --> 00:04:29,870
<i>Can I stay here?</i>

78
00:04:31,510 --> 00:04:34,760
<i>You have dance lessons after summer vacation.</i>

79
00:04:34,760 --> 00:04:37,700
<i>I don't want to attend dance lessons.</i>

80
00:04:37,700 --> 00:04:40,820
<i>Well, do you want to learn to paint like your sister?</i>

81
00:04:40,820 --> 00:04:43,650
<i>I don't want to learn to paint either.</i>

82
00:04:44,830 --> 00:04:47,060
<i>What do you want to learn?</i>

83
00:04:47,060 --> 00:04:50,950
<i>I want to raise chicks with you.</i>

84
00:04:54,510 --> 00:04:56,680
<i>What do you want to be when you grow up?</i>

85
00:04:56,680 --> 00:04:59,580
<i>Do you still want to rear chicks with me?</i>

86
00:04:59,580 --> 00:05:04,120
<i>I'll open a grocery store.</i>

87
00:05:04,640 --> 00:05:06,680
<i>Open a grocery store?</i>

88
00:05:06,680 --> 00:05:09,919
<i>I'll stock up on tons of ice creams and instant noodles.</i>

89
00:05:09,920 --> 00:05:13,430
<i>I'll eat them every day.</i>

90
00:05:15,510 --> 00:05:18,880
<i>If you eat your own products,</i>

91
00:05:18,880 --> 00:05:21,230
<i>how can you make money?</i>

92
00:05:21,230 --> 00:05:22,479
<i>I can.</i>

93
00:05:22,480 --> 00:05:24,040
<i>I'll open a huge supermarket.</i>

94
00:05:24,040 --> 00:05:27,360
<i>Then, I'll buy you roast chicken when I make money.</i>

95
00:05:28,720 --> 00:05:30,270
<i>Okay.</i>

96
00:05:31,160 --> 00:05:32,800
<i>I'll wait for you</i>

97
00:05:32,800 --> 00:05:35,380
<i>to set up a huge supermarket and earns tons of money.</i>

98
00:05:35,380 --> 00:05:38,000
<i>I'll wait for your roast chicken.</i>

99
00:05:40,040 --> 00:05:42,010
<i>Go to sleep, sweetie.</i>

100
00:05:59,480 --> 00:06:02,060
<i>It's feels amazing.</i>

101
00:06:22,160 --> 00:06:25,420
- Damai.
- What's wrong?

102
00:06:25,420 --> 00:06:28,120
Can I borrow your phone?

103
00:06:36,750 --> 00:06:38,310
Here you go. There's no passcode.

104
00:06:38,310 --> 00:06:40,040
Thanks.

105
00:06:48,870 --> 00:06:50,680
Who the heck is this?

106
00:06:50,680 --> 00:06:52,990
Exactly. Hello? Who is it?

107
00:06:52,990 --> 00:06:54,550
<i>Hello, Mom.</i>

108
00:06:54,550 --> 00:06:55,990
Dou!

109
00:06:55,990 --> 00:06:57,820
What's wrong? It's so late in the night.

110
00:06:57,820 --> 00:07:00,460
- What's going on?
- Did something happen?

111
00:07:50,240 --> 00:07:54,350
Hongdou called me in the middle of the night.

112
00:07:54,350 --> 00:07:56,480
I was scared out of my wits.

113
00:07:56,480 --> 00:08:00,290
In the end, she just asked me to visit you guys

114
00:08:00,290 --> 00:08:03,210
and buy you roast chicken.

115
00:08:03,870 --> 00:08:06,940
Did her granny appear in her dreams?

116
00:08:06,940 --> 00:08:09,200
The both of us are much closer to her.

117
00:08:09,200 --> 00:08:10,870
Why would she appear in Hongdou's dream?

118
00:08:10,870 --> 00:08:13,020
Grandparents love their grandchildren more.

119
00:08:13,020 --> 00:08:14,950
That's right.

120
00:08:18,870 --> 00:08:21,260
What's Hongmi doing recently?

121
00:08:21,260 --> 00:08:23,120
She's taking care of Lingdang.

122
00:08:23,120 --> 00:08:25,660
Lingdang is learning Chinese chess now.

123
00:08:25,660 --> 00:08:28,000
Wasn't she learning the piano?

124
00:08:28,000 --> 00:08:31,570
She's learning chess now that she's done with piano.

125
00:08:31,570 --> 00:08:35,460
Kexin is pregnant now.

126
00:08:35,460 --> 00:08:38,029
She's already started antenatal training.

127
00:08:38,030 --> 00:08:41,690
She reads poems to her belly every day.

128
00:08:41,690 --> 00:08:46,010
Her mother-in-law also bought some English books for her.

129
00:08:46,010 --> 00:08:49,100
Who can even understand a word of that?

130
00:08:49,100 --> 00:08:53,860
Time flies so quickly, generation after generation.

131
00:08:53,860 --> 00:08:57,900
- That's right.
- You're going to be a granny soon.

132
00:08:57,900 --> 00:08:59,800
Exactly.

133
00:09:46,790 --> 00:09:48,390
You're up?

134
00:09:48,390 --> 00:09:49,930
Do you know how to make a cat toy?

135
00:09:49,930 --> 00:09:51,200
I learned it from the internet.

136
00:09:51,200 --> 00:09:53,850
I'm just mimicking what I saw, so it's a little ugly.

137
00:10:00,080 --> 00:10:01,770
Thanks.

138
00:10:06,480 --> 00:10:08,150
I'm coming.

139
00:10:08,150 --> 00:10:10,870
I'll be there right away.

140
00:10:14,390 --> 00:10:16,080
Hongdou!

141
00:10:19,630 --> 00:10:20,629
Damai!

142
00:10:20,630 --> 00:10:23,360
Damai, you've been here for a month,

143
00:10:23,360 --> 00:10:26,100
but we've only met twice.

144
00:10:26,720 --> 00:10:29,650
You're free, right? Come and hang out with me. Let's make flower cakes.

145
00:10:29,650 --> 00:10:31,270
Those snacks with roses in them?

146
00:10:31,270 --> 00:10:33,070
Yes, and cow's milk cheese.

147
00:10:33,070 --> 00:10:35,949
- I bet you haven't heard of these before. Let's go.
- Okay!

148
00:10:35,949 --> 00:10:38,470
You guys go ahead. I'll stay here.

149
00:10:38,470 --> 00:10:40,149
Lassie,

150
00:10:40,150 --> 00:10:43,250
you coop yourself up in your room after you arrived and don't show your face.

151
00:10:43,250 --> 00:10:46,170
Look at your complexion. You look so frail!

152
00:10:46,170 --> 00:10:47,600
You have to take a stroll from time to time.

153
00:10:47,600 --> 00:10:49,020
- Let's go.
- I won't go.

154
00:10:49,020 --> 00:10:50,260
- I'm useless.
- Just come with us.

155
00:10:50,260 --> 00:10:52,719
It's very simple. You'll pick it up immediately.

156
00:10:52,720 --> 00:10:54,519
Jiahui, be good and stay home.

157
00:10:54,519 --> 00:10:55,690
I'm really useless.

158
00:10:55,690 --> 00:10:58,020
You'll master it right away! It's very simple!

159
00:10:58,020 --> 00:10:59,450
Let's go!

160
00:10:59,450 --> 00:11:02,640
There are flower cakes and cheese.

161
00:11:12,840 --> 00:11:15,050
Finally, some peace and quiet.

162
00:11:20,320 --> 00:11:22,020
Jiahui.

163
00:11:23,200 --> 00:11:25,220
I share your sentiments.

164
00:11:27,320 --> 00:11:29,850
You like quiet places too, don't you?

165
00:11:31,550 --> 00:11:33,750
We're the same.

166
00:11:36,840 --> 00:11:39,500
What a cute cat,

167
00:11:39,500 --> 00:11:43,990
but it must be uncomfortable to have this on your neck.

168
00:11:43,990 --> 00:11:45,980
I'll take it off for you.

169
00:11:46,600 --> 00:11:48,450
Lay here.

170
00:11:48,960 --> 00:11:51,630
I'll show you the Eight Silken Movements exercise.

171
00:12:42,440 --> 00:12:45,060
Baoping, we're here!

172
00:12:45,060 --> 00:12:47,720
I even brought helpers over.

173
00:12:49,000 --> 00:12:50,909
The guests at the courtyard.

174
00:12:50,910 --> 00:12:54,249
- This is Xiaochun's mom, Aunty Baoping.
- Hello.
- Hello.

175
00:12:54,249 --> 00:12:57,130
This is Hongdou and Damai.

176
00:12:57,130 --> 00:12:58,510
I know you two.

177
00:12:58,510 --> 00:12:59,910
A'Yao told me about you guys.

178
00:12:59,910 --> 00:13:02,260
- I'll make some tea for you.
- It's fine. We aren't thirsty.

179
00:13:02,260 --> 00:13:03,750
What are you making?

180
00:13:03,750 --> 00:13:05,160
I'm making cow's cheese milk.

181
00:13:05,160 --> 00:13:06,030
Cow's cheese milk?

182
00:13:06,030 --> 00:13:07,740
Is it the same as the fried cheese sold on the streets?

183
00:13:07,740 --> 00:13:08,959
That's right.

184
00:13:08,960 --> 00:13:10,749
Here, have a taste.

185
00:13:10,750 --> 00:13:12,410
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

186
00:13:17,360 --> 00:13:19,150
It tastes like ordinary cheese.

187
00:13:19,150 --> 00:13:22,110
In the past, we'd sell these because we were poor.

188
00:13:22,110 --> 00:13:23,440
We seldom make them now.

189
00:13:23,440 --> 00:13:26,719
We used to hang them all over the yard if we made too much.

190
00:13:26,720 --> 00:13:28,030
Aunty Baoping, you're impressive.

191
00:13:28,030 --> 00:13:30,400
It's nothing. I was just raising the family.

192
00:13:30,400 --> 00:13:31,920
All done.

193
00:13:31,920 --> 00:13:33,440
Let's get to work.

194
00:13:33,440 --> 00:13:35,250
Do you need help?

195
00:13:35,250 --> 00:13:38,000
Wash your hands first. Meet me in the kitchen.

196
00:13:50,150 --> 00:13:51,720
Are you using fresh roses?

197
00:13:51,720 --> 00:13:52,790
Yes.

198
00:13:52,790 --> 00:13:53,940
Here you go.

199
00:13:53,940 --> 00:13:56,150
Have a whiff. Isn't it fragrant?

200
00:13:58,030 --> 00:14:01,239
There are two ways to making the fillings for flower cakes.

201
00:14:01,240 --> 00:14:04,840
One way is to make rose jam a week in advance

202
00:14:04,840 --> 00:14:05,790
and fill up the cakes.

203
00:14:05,790 --> 00:14:08,220
The other way is to make fresh flower cakes.

204
00:14:08,220 --> 00:14:11,739
There are lard oil, paste powder, and sugar in it.

205
00:14:11,739 --> 00:14:12,790
We mix everything together.

206
00:14:12,790 --> 00:14:16,480
Right now, I'm going to mix them thoroughly.

207
00:14:16,480 --> 00:14:20,430
Are you making flower cakes and cheese for a celebration?

208
00:14:20,430 --> 00:14:22,700
Nope.

209
00:14:22,700 --> 00:14:27,289
Aunty Baoping's son, Xia Xia, is meeting a friend in Shanghai.

210
00:14:27,289 --> 00:14:30,150
Baoping wants to make some local delicacies

211
00:14:30,150 --> 00:14:33,420
for his son's Shanghainese friend to try.

212
00:14:33,420 --> 00:14:37,270
My children, Dayang and Xiao Xi, haven't been home in ages.

213
00:14:37,270 --> 00:14:40,620
So, I'll make extras to send to them.

214
00:14:40,620 --> 00:14:44,550
Such food can be bought,

215
00:14:44,550 --> 00:14:47,980
but handmade ones taste like home.

216
00:14:48,920 --> 00:14:50,669
Mix everything together first.

217
00:14:50,670 --> 00:14:53,130
Then, we can use them as fillings.

218
00:14:56,360 --> 00:14:59,440
Should I leave early if I want to board a boat at Huangpu River?

219
00:15:00,840 --> 00:15:03,730
Is there anything yummy there? Are they expensive?

220
00:15:03,730 --> 00:15:05,650
I don't know.

221
00:15:06,270 --> 00:15:07,620
Haven't you been on that boat?

222
00:15:07,620 --> 00:15:10,710
I have, but as a child. I've already forgotten everything.

223
00:15:10,710 --> 00:15:12,920
Are you sure you're from Shanghai?

224
00:15:12,920 --> 00:15:14,800
Should I show you my ID card?

225
00:15:14,800 --> 00:15:16,389
No, thanks.

226
00:15:16,390 --> 00:15:18,340
You're welcome.

227
00:15:19,000 --> 00:15:21,290
I said you're welcome.

228
00:15:24,870 --> 00:15:27,100
Have you eaten this waffle?

229
00:15:27,630 --> 00:15:29,910
I don't know. Probably not.

230
00:15:30,670 --> 00:15:31,840
Why are you so clueless?

231
00:15:31,840 --> 00:15:35,710
My Shanghainese friend knows all the best places.

232
00:15:35,710 --> 00:15:38,900
Well, ask him. Don't come to me.

233
00:15:38,900 --> 00:15:41,800
He's working now, so I feel bad bothering him.

234
00:15:43,030 --> 00:15:45,360
Don't you feel bad bothering me?

235
00:15:47,560 --> 00:15:49,160
<i>[Brother Kaiwen (Yang Kaiwen)]</i>

236
00:15:57,440 --> 00:15:59,900
<i>[The principal balance is ¥1000, so the profit is ¥300. That should be enough to treat your friend to a meal.]</i>

237
00:16:08,800 --> 00:16:09,800
<i>[Wow, that's a lot. Thanks, bro.]</i>

238
00:16:09,800 --> 00:16:12,000
<i>[That isn't much. You can open an account yourself, since keeping cash is just a waste. I'll help you make money.]</i>

239
00:16:15,240 --> 00:16:16,389
Na Na.

240
00:16:16,390 --> 00:16:17,740
Do you buy stocks?

241
00:16:17,740 --> 00:16:20,900
No, I buy trade funds.

242
00:16:20,900 --> 00:16:22,870
Does it make money?

243
00:16:22,870 --> 00:16:24,150
It's hard to say.

244
00:16:24,150 --> 00:16:27,500
The market is good recently, so I earned some money.

245
00:16:28,200 --> 00:16:29,880
Are you planning to buy stocks?

246
00:16:29,880 --> 00:16:31,780
Do you think I can?

247
00:16:32,750 --> 00:16:35,040
No way. It's too risky.

248
00:16:35,040 --> 00:16:37,030
A clueless guy like you

249
00:16:37,030 --> 00:16:40,840
will be gobbled up by them the moment you enter the market.

250
00:16:47,000 --> 00:16:48,239
Xie Xiaoxia.

251
00:16:48,240 --> 00:16:49,880
- Sister.
- You're slacking here again, aren't you?

252
00:16:49,880 --> 00:16:51,450
You're about to leave soon.

253
00:16:51,450 --> 00:16:53,490
- Can't you help Mom with some work?
- Yeah.

254
00:16:54,650 --> 00:16:58,390
Don't just say that. I'll wallop you if you do this again.

255
00:16:59,440 --> 00:17:01,500
His heart is no longer here.

256
00:17:01,500 --> 00:17:03,980
It's useless to scold him.

257
00:17:05,960 --> 00:17:09,350
When can my brother become sensible?

258
00:17:10,070 --> 00:17:12,400
A drama's male lead said this.

259
00:17:12,400 --> 00:17:15,050
People turn into adults in a snap.

260
00:17:15,050 --> 00:17:16,570
A snap?

261
00:17:16,570 --> 00:17:18,050
When's that?

262
00:17:18,050 --> 00:17:22,290
It's a moment only known to you and nobody else.

263
00:17:22,290 --> 00:17:24,140
That's what he said.

264
00:17:24,680 --> 00:17:29,719
Well, I reckon my brother will grow up

265
00:17:29,720 --> 00:17:35,399
when he passes away and the coffin cover slams down over him.

266
00:17:35,400 --> 00:17:37,159
What's with that nonsense?

267
00:17:37,160 --> 00:17:38,350
You're so mean.

268
00:17:38,350 --> 00:17:40,540
Are you sure you're his sister?

269
00:17:45,000 --> 00:17:47,190
- A'Peng.
- Hey!

270
00:17:47,190 --> 00:17:48,269
Did you see A'Yuan?

271
00:17:48,270 --> 00:17:50,140
He is in the stables.

272
00:17:50,920 --> 00:17:51,640
Take care of him.

273
00:17:51,640 --> 00:17:53,640
Don't worry.

274
00:18:04,240 --> 00:18:05,530
Uncle Zeqing.

275
00:18:05,530 --> 00:18:07,080
Did you see A'Yuan?

276
00:18:07,080 --> 00:18:08,999
He said he has a stomach ache, so I let him go home.

277
00:18:09,000 --> 00:18:10,349
Did something happen?

278
00:18:10,350 --> 00:18:12,620
It's nothing. You can get on with your work.

279
00:18:23,200 --> 00:18:25,520
Hello, Aunty.

280
00:18:25,520 --> 00:18:27,140
It's me.

281
00:18:27,140 --> 00:18:28,879
I'm at the horse ranch.

282
00:18:28,880 --> 00:18:31,510
A'Yuan isn't here. I guess he went home.

283
00:18:31,510 --> 00:18:33,479
<i>What's going on?</i>

284
00:18:33,480 --> 00:18:36,480
<i>Your dad sent him to the countryside to work and become sensible.</i>

285
00:18:36,480 --> 00:18:39,589
<i>He's supposed to come running back to school after experiencing such labor.</i>

286
00:18:39,590 --> 00:18:42,580
<i>Why is he enjoying life now?</i>

287
00:18:42,580 --> 00:18:44,679
You were the ones who set him free.

288
00:18:44,680 --> 00:18:46,140
I can do nothing about it.

289
00:18:46,140 --> 00:18:49,970
<i>As his brother, you can hit him if he's naughty.</i>

290
00:18:50,590 --> 00:18:52,069
Hit him?

291
00:18:52,070 --> 00:18:55,340
If I hurt him, you'll be upset.

292
00:18:55,340 --> 00:18:56,959
<i>Well, don't stop your granny.</i>

293
00:18:56,960 --> 00:18:59,070
<i>Let your granny hit him.</i>

294
00:18:59,070 --> 00:19:02,380
Things aren't that severe.

295
00:19:02,380 --> 00:19:04,199
If he really doesn't want to go back,

296
00:19:04,199 --> 00:19:07,190
I'll find a school for him here in Dali.

297
00:19:07,190 --> 00:19:09,110
Don't worry.

298
00:19:09,110 --> 00:19:11,160
Okay. Bye.

299
00:19:28,970 --> 00:19:30,740
Go!

300
00:19:35,653 --> 00:19:40,700
♫ <i>There are stars in my journey</i> ♫

301
00:19:40,700 --> 00:19:44,000
♫ <i>There are rainbows</i> ♫

302
00:19:45,313 --> 00:19:48,820
♫ <i>We lose the chance to hug</i> ♫

303
00:19:48,820 --> 00:19:53,800
♫ <i>A breeze wafts through some parts of the world</i> ♫

304
00:19:53,800 --> 00:19:56,900
♫ <i>Hidden spots make my heart flutter</i> ♫

305
00:19:58,400 --> 00:20:01,980
♫ <i>Whose dream will be fulfilled??</i> ♫

306
00:20:01,980 --> 00:20:04,000
♫ <i>In the street where rain and sunshine shower down</i> ♫

307
00:20:04,000 --> 00:20:06,030
Well done, Hongdou!

308
00:20:06,030 --> 00:20:07,400
You're good at this.

309
00:20:07,400 --> 00:20:09,010
Is it too small?

310
00:20:09,010 --> 00:20:10,780
It'll do.

311
00:20:11,447 --> 00:20:13,640
♫ <i>We say goodbye</i> ♫

312
00:20:13,640 --> 00:20:16,360
You can alter the temperature here.

313
00:20:16,360 --> 00:20:18,050
Let me do it.

314
00:20:18,050 --> 00:20:20,610
Add the winter cherries.

315
00:20:20,610 --> 00:20:25,160
♫ <i>Although the seasons go by</i> ♫

316
00:20:25,160 --> 00:20:28,736
♫ <i>I'll still love passionately like a youth</i> ♫

317
00:20:28,736 --> 00:20:33,080
♫ <i>Sometimes I find I fall in love</i> ♫

318
00:20:33,800 --> 00:20:37,920
