00:20:43,383 --> 00:20:47,480
♫ <i>Sometimes I need a beautiful smile</i> ♫

321
00:20:48,504 --> 00:20:52,500
♫ <i>Although the seasons go by</i> ♫

322
00:20:52,974 --> 00:20:56,560
♫ <i>I'll still love passionately like a youth</i> ♫

323
00:20:56,560 --> 00:21:00,589
♫ <i>Sometimes I find I fall in love</i> ♫

324
00:21:00,590 --> 00:21:02,610
I'll add the sugar. Mix it with both hands.

325
00:21:02,610 --> 00:21:05,920
♫ <i>Make a little wish and pray</i> ♫

326
00:21:05,920 --> 00:21:11,060
♫ Maybe things will go your way<i> ♫</i>

327
00:21:23,160 --> 00:21:25,820
Here it is!

328
00:21:25,820 --> 00:21:26,640
Come on.

329
00:21:26,640 --> 00:21:27,999
Be careful. It's hot.

330
00:21:28,000 --> 00:21:29,630
Don't touch the tray.

331
00:21:29,630 --> 00:21:31,310
Have a taste.

332
00:21:37,261 --> 00:21:39,031
Baoping!

333
00:21:42,350 --> 00:21:44,350
Your oven isn't good.

334
00:21:44,350 --> 00:21:45,640
I bet it's cheap.

335
00:21:45,640 --> 00:21:48,040
Look, it's too shabby.

336
00:21:48,040 --> 00:21:50,700
This isn't crispy at all!

337
00:21:50,700 --> 00:21:52,549
Next time, bake at my house.

338
00:21:52,550 --> 00:21:55,269
We can use the huge oven Xiao Xi bought for me.

339
00:21:55,270 --> 00:21:59,190
It's sturdy and has many functions.

340
00:21:59,190 --> 00:22:00,269
Enough.

341
00:22:00,270 --> 00:22:03,070
You like everything that Xiao Xi buys for you.

342
00:22:03,070 --> 00:22:04,760
You're not wrong.

343
00:22:04,760 --> 00:22:05,790
Is it delicious?

344
00:22:05,790 --> 00:22:06,980
Yes.

345
00:22:06,980 --> 00:22:08,009
It tastes great.

346
00:22:08,009 --> 00:22:10,380
It'll be even more delicious with a better oven.

347
00:22:10,380 --> 00:22:12,839
Hongdou, hand this to A'Yao.

348
00:22:12,839 --> 00:22:14,000
Granny likes to eat this.

349
00:22:14,000 --> 00:22:15,800
Okay, no problem.

350
00:22:15,800 --> 00:22:19,830
Aunty Baoping, can you give me the few pieces I made?

351
00:22:19,830 --> 00:22:21,069
No problem.

352
00:22:21,070 --> 00:22:23,270
When it's dry, I'll pack them for you.

353
00:22:23,270 --> 00:22:24,680
You can let your parents have a taste.

354
00:22:24,680 --> 00:22:25,750
Thanks.

355
00:22:25,750 --> 00:22:29,550
Aunty Baoping, we only ate and took these gifts without helping much.

356
00:22:29,550 --> 00:22:32,140
I'm happy to have you here.

357
00:22:32,140 --> 00:22:33,770
- We'll get going.
- Okay.

358
00:22:33,770 --> 00:22:34,940
- Goodbye.
- Watch your step.

359
00:22:34,940 --> 00:22:37,550
- Okay.
- Bye-bye, Aunty Baoping.

360
00:23:10,880 --> 00:23:15,159
Shower! Shower! A nice shower!

361
00:23:15,160 --> 00:23:16,440
My dear brother.

362
00:23:16,440 --> 00:23:18,180
What are we eating tonight?

363
00:23:18,180 --> 00:23:21,000
What are we eating?

364
00:23:21,000 --> 00:23:23,480
- Braised chicken.
- Braised chicken!

365
00:23:23,480 --> 00:23:24,640
Where's Granny?

366
00:23:24,640 --> 00:23:26,590
She went to visit others.

367
00:23:29,790 --> 00:23:31,350
Smells amazing!

368
00:23:31,350 --> 00:23:33,850
Brother, where's the rice?

369
00:23:33,850 --> 00:23:36,150
I'm heating the leftover rice from lunch.

370
00:23:36,150 --> 00:23:37,800
Come over here first.

371
00:23:37,800 --> 00:23:39,690
I need to talk to you.

372
00:23:41,480 --> 00:23:43,490
Here we go again.

373
00:24:02,240 --> 00:24:04,540
Stop staring at me and talk.

374
00:24:05,640 --> 00:24:07,930
I asked a friend in the Old Town about school—

375
00:24:07,930 --> 00:24:09,890
I won't go!

376
00:24:09,890 --> 00:24:11,960
I won't go even if you beat me to death!

377
00:24:14,200 --> 00:24:15,479
<i>I'm not going!</i>

378
00:24:15,480 --> 00:24:16,679
<i>Stop inquiring!</i>

379
00:24:16,680 --> 00:24:18,820
<i>I suck at studying! Transferring schools won't make a difference!</i>

380
00:24:18,820 --> 00:24:20,879
<i>I'll still be mocked!</i>

381
00:24:20,880 --> 00:24:22,310
<i>Well, go back to Kunming then.</i>

382
00:24:22,310 --> 00:24:23,649
<i>At least finish high school.</i>

383
00:24:23,649 --> 00:24:25,880
<i>I won‘t! You can't make me go!</i>

384
00:24:25,880 --> 00:24:27,549
It's no big deal.

385
00:24:27,550 --> 00:24:29,639
Being so whiny is even more embarrassing!

386
00:24:29,640 --> 00:24:31,679
I bet they'll laugh at me in secret!

387
00:24:31,680 --> 00:24:34,349
I've already become the laughing stock of the whole school!

388
00:24:34,350 --> 00:24:37,000
High school is so stressful. They don't have time to be mocking you.

389
00:24:37,000 --> 00:24:39,100
Do you think you're some celebrity?

390
00:24:39,100 --> 00:24:40,959
It's easy for you to blabber.

391
00:24:40,960 --> 00:24:45,620
My reputation is already in tatters now!

392
00:24:45,620 --> 00:24:48,829
I'd rather die than go back to Kunming!

393
00:24:48,830 --> 00:24:50,720
You'd rather die?

394
00:24:50,720 --> 00:24:53,070
You just pooped in your pants during class because of a stomach ache.

395
00:24:53,070 --> 00:24:55,029
Xie Zhiyao!

396
00:24:55,030 --> 00:24:58,029
If you talk about it again, I'll kill myself!

397
00:24:58,030 --> 00:25:00,720
Well, kill yourself after you finish high school!

398
00:25:14,590 --> 00:25:16,480
Aunty Baoping asked me to bring over flower cakes.

399
00:25:16,480 --> 00:25:17,870
I'll get going now.

400
00:25:17,870 --> 00:25:20,330
Wait! You can't go!

401
00:25:20,330 --> 00:25:21,789
Xie Zhiyuan, what are you doing?

402
00:25:21,790 --> 00:25:22,789
Let go of her.

403
00:25:22,790 --> 00:25:24,239
No, I won't!

404
00:25:24,240 --> 00:25:25,399
I won't leave.

405
00:25:25,400 --> 00:25:27,760
Are you okay? You aren't injured, are you?

406
00:25:48,310 --> 00:25:50,210
Why are you laughing?

407
00:25:51,510 --> 00:25:53,829
Can't people laugh after your pooping incident?

408
00:25:53,830 --> 00:25:56,200
Stop talking about it!

409
00:25:58,000 --> 00:25:59,720
Talk to him nicely.

410
00:25:59,720 --> 00:26:01,650
Don't hit him.

411
00:26:01,650 --> 00:26:03,239
She can't leave.

412
00:26:03,240 --> 00:26:05,160
What if she blabbers and ruins my reputation?

413
00:26:05,160 --> 00:26:06,550
Who do you think you are?

414
00:26:06,550 --> 00:26:08,400
Ruin your reputation? Do you even have that?

415
00:26:08,400 --> 00:26:10,510
- Why don't I...
- Don't worry.

416
00:26:10,510 --> 00:26:12,880
I won't tell a soul.

417
00:26:14,000 --> 00:26:15,960
I don't trust you.

418
00:26:15,960 --> 00:26:16,959
Fine.

419
00:26:16,960 --> 00:26:19,760
Tell me what you want. I'll go along with your wishes.

420
00:26:22,400 --> 00:26:24,000
Well...

421
00:26:32,300 --> 00:26:34,270
What are you doing?

422
00:26:39,720 --> 00:26:40,919
Have you had dinner?

423
00:26:40,920 --> 00:26:42,750
Not yet.

424
00:26:42,750 --> 00:26:44,439
Let's eat together.

425
00:26:44,440 --> 00:26:46,959
I brought this braised chicken over from Aunty Hua's home.

426
00:26:46,960 --> 00:26:48,830
That explains the fragrance.

427
00:26:48,830 --> 00:26:50,110
It's my lucky day.

428
00:26:50,110 --> 00:26:52,780
- Take a seat. I'll get the rice.
- Okay.

429
00:26:56,480 --> 00:26:59,100
I'm going to take some rice.

430
00:27:12,000 --> 00:27:13,720
I won't leave.

431
00:27:13,720 --> 00:27:15,510
I'll have dinner here.

432
00:27:18,510 --> 00:27:20,820
Isn't Granny home today?

433
00:27:28,750 --> 00:27:30,440
Let's have dinner.

434
00:27:35,040 --> 00:27:36,930
It's still warm.

435
00:27:39,030 --> 00:27:40,720
Aren't we waiting for Granny?

436
00:27:40,720 --> 00:27:41,960
She went out for a stroll.

437
00:27:41,960 --> 00:27:44,110
I'll pick her up later.

438
00:27:44,110 --> 00:27:45,680
Okay.

439
00:27:47,920 --> 00:27:50,740
Did Aunty A'Gui drag you to be her helper?

440
00:27:50,740 --> 00:27:54,340
She was probably worried that Damai and I were bored, so she invited us over.

441
00:27:54,340 --> 00:27:55,590
Was it fun?

442
00:27:55,590 --> 00:27:57,380
Yes.

443
00:27:58,830 --> 00:28:02,639
Get Aunty Baoping bring you to the warehouse.

444
00:28:02,640 --> 00:28:04,679
The warehouse? Where's that?

445
00:28:04,680 --> 00:28:07,730
It's her workplace. An e-commerce warehouse.

446
00:28:07,730 --> 00:28:09,580
Have you packed products before?

447
00:28:09,580 --> 00:28:11,150
Nope.

448
00:28:11,150 --> 00:28:13,620
Don't ask me to join in labor.

449
00:28:13,620 --> 00:28:16,970
Fine. I'll look for you when there's food.

450
00:28:16,970 --> 00:28:18,920
Does it taste good?

451
00:28:20,200 --> 00:28:22,269
The chicken is so tender.

452
00:28:22,270 --> 00:28:23,770
It's delicious.

453
00:28:23,770 --> 00:28:25,109
At such a time,

454
00:28:25,110 --> 00:28:28,140
a cup of cherry wine that Granny made

455
00:28:28,140 --> 00:28:30,069
would be perfect.

456
00:28:30,070 --> 00:28:31,920
Cherry wine?

457
00:28:33,070 --> 00:28:34,090
Go.

458
00:28:34,090 --> 00:28:36,680
Fetch the wine on the kitchen shelf.

459
00:28:37,880 --> 00:28:38,829
Go on.

460
00:28:38,830 --> 00:28:40,390
Why are you in a daze?

461
00:29:37,240 --> 00:29:39,000
Half a cup is enough.

462
00:29:39,000 --> 00:29:41,550
Although this wine is sweet, it contains a lot of alcohol.

463
00:29:41,550 --> 00:29:43,250
Drink it slowly.

464
00:29:50,160 --> 00:29:51,670
The cherry taste is so intense.

465
00:29:51,670 --> 00:29:54,159
Wild cherries are sour when eaten,

466
00:29:54,160 --> 00:29:56,270
but they're great for making wine.

467
00:30:24,710 --> 00:30:27,160
Keep it a secret. You promised me.

468
00:30:27,160 --> 00:30:30,000
Don't worry. I'll keep it a secret.

469
00:30:32,640 --> 00:30:35,780
Sorry. He's a reckless boy. Please forgive him.

470
00:30:35,780 --> 00:30:36,719
It's nothing.

471
00:30:36,720 --> 00:30:38,549
Actually, I feel sorry for him.

472
00:30:38,550 --> 00:30:39,720
You feel sorry for him?

473
00:30:39,720 --> 00:30:41,310
How about feeling sorry for me?

474
00:30:41,310 --> 00:30:43,309
He's torturing me to death.

475
00:30:43,310 --> 00:30:44,270
That's true.

476
00:30:44,270 --> 00:30:48,500
Teenagers think their self-esteem is the world at sixteen or seventeen.

477
00:30:48,500 --> 00:30:50,900
Besides, he humiliated himself so terribly in class.

478
00:30:50,900 --> 00:30:54,360
What if he has a girl he likes?

479
00:30:54,360 --> 00:30:57,940
I understand why he wants to quit school.

480
00:30:57,940 --> 00:30:59,959
He wants to quit school after such a small setback.

481
00:30:59,960 --> 00:31:01,639
He has a long life ahead of him.

482
00:31:01,640 --> 00:31:03,719
What if he encounters something even more humiliating?

483
00:31:03,720 --> 00:31:06,680
He won't understand your reasoning now.

484
00:31:10,200 --> 00:31:12,440
Do you have siblings?

485
00:31:12,440 --> 00:31:14,320
Yeah, I have an elder sister.

486
00:31:14,320 --> 00:31:17,940
She's five years old than me, and her child is in kindergarten.

487
00:31:18,550 --> 00:31:20,159
Five years older?

488
00:31:20,160 --> 00:31:21,439
That's much better.

489
00:31:21,440 --> 00:31:23,390
How is that better?

490
00:31:23,390 --> 00:31:25,050
Do you quarrel, too?

491
00:31:25,050 --> 00:31:27,509
How are sibling quarrels related to age?

492
00:31:27,510 --> 00:31:28,680
Well, what's the crux?

493
00:31:28,680 --> 00:31:30,740
Personalities.

494
00:31:30,740 --> 00:31:32,920
Doesn't that mean you'll fight for life?

495
00:31:38,790 --> 00:31:40,390
Be careful.

496
00:31:40,390 --> 00:31:43,750
♫ <i>Listen to the rain falling into the silent forest</i> ♫

497
00:31:45,680 --> 00:31:50,840
♫ <i>Enjoy the mountainous landscape at sunset</i> ♫

498
00:31:53,080 --> 00:31:59,359
♫ <i>The raindrops from the roof drip into my eyes quietly</i> ♫

499
00:31:59,359 --> 00:32:04,860
♫ <i>The world is like a quiet island</i> ♫

500
00:32:07,921 --> 00:32:12,760
♫ <i>The sky is turning bright without a sound</i> ♫

501
00:32:15,248 --> 00:32:20,300
♫ <i>Waiting for the seabirds to call forth the ripples</i> ♫
